de.learnlib.parallelism

Interface ParallelOracle<I,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - input symbol type
    O - output type
    All Superinterfaces:
    MembershipOracle<I,O>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicParallelOracle, StaticParallelOracle

    public interface ParallelOracle<I,O>
extends MembershipOracle<I,O>
    Basic interface for MembershipOracles that can process queries in parallel.

    Parallel oracles usually use one or more dedicated worker threads in which the processing of queries is performed. Since these do not have a defined life span, they must be terminated explicitly using shutdown() or shutdownNow().

    Author:
    Malte Isberner
